    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Boxes, usually of medium to large size, intended for the storage of linens, clothing, books, food, artifacts, or any other item. They are usually lidded or have flaps that allow the box to be closed. They may be made of cardboard, wood, metal, plastic, wicker, or another material.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用於儲存居家常用亞麻織品、衣物、書本、食物、工藝品等物件的箱子，尺寸多為中型至大型，多具有蓋子或可封住箱子的掀板，材質可能為紙板、木頭、金屬、塑膠、植物枝條或其他材料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dozen, meestal van middelgroot tot groot formaat, om linnengoed, kleding, boeken, voedsel, artefacten of andere voorwerpen in te bewaren. Ze hebben meestal kleppen of een deksel waarmee ze kunnen worden gesloten. Ze kunnen gemaakt zijn van karton, hout, metaal, plastic, vlechtwerk of een ander materiaal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
